The article discusses the importance of National Cancer Control Month and calls on all Americans to join the movement to end cancer. It highlights the progress made in the fight against cancer, such as the reduction in the death rate and the discovery of prevention and early detection measures. However, it also acknowledges that cancer still claims the lives of many Americans, particularly in communities of color. The article emphasizes the need to make treatments more affordable and accessible, and mentions initiatives such as the Advanced Research Projects Agency for Health and the expansion of the Affordable Care Act. It also emphasizes the importance of prevention, including efforts to reduce smoking and promote healthy eating and exercise habits. The article encourages Americans to catch up on missed screening appointments and provides resources for information and support. Finally, President Biden proclaims April 2023 as National Cancer Control Month and calls on individuals and organizations to increase awareness and take action against cancer.